Are you ready to elevate your career in a dynamic and innovative environment? Join Allianz, where a top-notch team and exceptional opportunities are waiting for you.  


**What will you do?**
We are seeking a talented and motivated Financial Data Scientist to join our team. In this role, you will focus on implementing data-driven automation into our financial processes and conduct various quantitative analyses to support our business operations. This is a unique opportunity to work at the intersection of data science and finance, driving efficiency and innovation in our financial operations.  


* Develop and implement data-driven automation solutions for financial processes to improve efficiency and accuracy;
* Perform quantitative analyses to support financial decision-making and strategic planning;
* Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify opportunities for automation and data analysis;
* Design and maintain financial models, dashboards, and reports;
* Analyze large datasets to extract insights and inform business strategies;
* Ensure data integrity and accuracy in all financial analysis and reporting;
* Stay updated with the latest industry trends and advancements in data science and financial technology.




**What do we offer you?**
Besides a top-notch team, at Allianz you also get every opportunity to create a good work-life balance. Not only are we flexible with an average of 60% working from home, but you also get the flexibility to schedule hours to suit your life. If you want to work out during lunchtime or pick up the kids in between meetings, that's no problem at all. You also get the opportunity to work 25 days a year from a holiday address in Europe.
Are you ready for something new after some time? There are plenty of career opportunities within Allianz! You can prepare yourself through 10,000+ training courses via Linkedin Learning and our own training programmes. In addition, you are entitled to:
* A good market-based salary;
* 8% holiday pay and a gratuity of 12.5% of annual salary;
* 25 holidays based on a 38-hour working week and the possibility of accruing 13-ADV days;
